title.narrative: HEALTH SYSTEM STRENGTHENING

description.narrative: Health system strengthened to deliver integrated and quality maternal and child health, nutrition and wellbeing services, and families are empowered to utilise quality services, which contributes to Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care (Covid), Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: All boys and girls and families have equitable access to and utilize quality integrated social services that ensure survival and health, provision of nurturing care and protection from adversity

description.narrative: Capitalizing on the past 5-years investments, UNICEF has continued to support the MoH to respond to numerous ongoing and emerging challenges to bolster the health system, including country’s response to COVID-19 pandemic. Work included support to development of National COVID-19 Vaccines Deployment plan and import of vaccines through COVAX, increasing vaccines demand through public campaign, knowledge generation on capacity of health workers for inter-personal communication skills on routine immunization, behavioural drivers of MMR1 vaccine hesitancy, digitalization of the recording and reporting system for home visitors and functional analysis of the home visiting system. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:21/01/2022
